set -x → Show each command before running. (Debugging mode)
set -e → Stop the script immediately if any command fails.

Example 1: Debugging with set -x
#!/bin/bash
set -x
echo "Step 1: Listing files"
ls
echo "Step 2: Showing current path"
pwd


Example 2: Stopping with set -e
#!/bin/bash
set -e
echo "Starting script..."
ls /not_exist   # Error → script stops
echo "This won’t run"
